Date: Mon, 23 Feb 1998 15:59:48 -0700
From: Hal Nash <HNASH@wwcc.cc.wy.us>

On the contrary, the ease by which we find organic molecules in outer space
gets us at least one or two steps toward life. Carl Sagan estimated that
the number of planets in the Milky Way galaxy suitable for life to be 3 x
10E11. This number is not infinitesimal.
--
Hal B. Nash
